[1] USA: summary. 26 states report measles cases
Date: Mon 27 May 2019
Source: KOBI-TV NBC5 [abridged, edited]
https://kobi5.com/news/26-states-report-measles-cases-102811/


Over half of the states in the country [USA] are dealing with measles. The latest numbers from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) show that 940 cases have been confirmed in 26 states as of last [Fri 24 May 2019], an increase of 60 cases from the previous week.

Maine and New Mexico are the latest states to report cases of the highly infectious disease. The hardest hit state continues to be New York, where there are nearly 800 cases. The majority of the patients are children who have not been vaccinated.

The states that have reported cases to CDC are Arizona, California, Colorado, Connecticut, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kentucky, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, Missouri, New Mexico, Nevada, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Oklahoma, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Texas, Tennessee, and Washington.

