[3] USA (King county, Washington state)
Date: Sat 25 May 2019
Source: King County: Public health news and blog [abridged, edited]
https://www.kingcounty.gov/depts/health/news/2019/May/25-measles.aspx


Summary
-------
A King county resident has tested positive for measles. All exposure locations in King county, including those from previous cases, are updated at http://kingcounty.gov/measles/cases.

Seattle & King county is investigating a new measles case with possible exposures in King county. The King county resident, a 6 month old child, was taken to Seattle Children's Hospital while she was contagious. This is the 5th King county case identified this month [May 2019], bringing the total to 8 recent measles cases in Washington state residents. This case was a household contact of a person diagnosed with measles earlier this month and was not exposed to measles in the community.

