[14] New Zealand: outbreak update
Date: Mon 27 May 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/auckland-measles-outbreak-update-syphilis-increases-72816/


The Auckland Regional Public Health Service, in a measles outbreak today [27 May 2019], reports the outbreak case tally is now 71 since the beginning of the year [2019]. Nationally, New Zealand has reported 158 measles cases year to date, 147 were unvaccinated or under vaccinated.

Outbreaks of measles have also been reported in Canterbury and Waikato. Cases have also been reported in the Bay of Plenty, Lakes, Northland, Capital, and Coast and Southern DHB [district health boards] areas.

