[15] China (Hong Kong)
Date: Tue 28 May 2019 10:14 PM HKT
Source: South China Morning Post [abridged edited]
https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3012194/measles-latest-bvlgari-sales-assistant-harbour


A sales assistant in Hong Kong who works at a shop next to the Gucci outlet hit earlier by a measles outbreak has emerged as the latest victim of the disease. The latest case pushed the total number of measles cases in the city to 75 so far this year [2019], up from 15 last year [2018] and 4 in 2017, according to the Centre for Health Protection.

The 32 year old man works at the Bulgari store in Harbour City shopping centre in the tourist district of Tsim Sha Tsui. 6 staff members at the Gucci shop next door contracted the disease earlier this month [May 2019]. A centre spokesman said on [Tue 28 May 2019]: "It is premature to speculate if the disease had spread from [Gucci]. The man told us that he believed he had not contacted any measles patients."

Despite being of previous good health and said to have received two doses of measles vaccination, the sales assistant developed a fever and runny nose last [Thu 21 May 2019], before a rash emerged 2 days later. He went to see a private doctor on [Sun 26 May 2019] and was referred to the Princess Margaret Hospital, where he was admitted that day. A laboratory test of his respiratory specimen proved positive for the measles virus. The centre said he was in a stable condition.

There are more than 30 people working at the luxury goods store. The patient lives with his mother and his girlfriend, neither of whom had any symptoms but have been put under medical surveillance. The man had no relevant travel history, according to the centre.

In a statement released on [Tue 28 May 2019], the centre said: "Upon notification of the case, the [centre] immediately commenced epidemiological investigations and conducted relevant contact tracing. Investigations are ongoing." A spokesman for the Bulgari outlet in Harbour City could not be reached for comment at press time on [Tue 28 May 2019]. Following the outbreak at the Gucci store, the management company of Harbour City deployed a team of cleaners for disinfection.

A spokesman for Harbour City confirmed it was told on Monday evening [27 May 2019] of the measles case at Bulgari. "Harbour City will continue to take on extra cleaning at the common area in the mall," the spokesman said.

While global measles deaths have decreased by 84% worldwide in recent years -- from 550 100 deaths in 2000 to 89 780 in 2016 -- it is still common in many developing countries, especially in parts of Africa and Asia.

In Hong Kong, health authorities were put on high alert after a cluster of 29 measles cases at the city's international airport were reported since [22 Mar 2019]. In an emergency operation, the centre vaccinated more than 8500 of those working at the airport. On [17 May 2019], the centre announced that the outbreak of measles infection at the Hong Kong airport had concluded.

[byline: Ng Kang-chung]

